27/05/2004
MAMAIA, Romania -- The government kicked off the two-day 11th summit of Central European heads of state on Thursday (27 May), aimed at boosting co-operation among participants.
Representatives from 17 countries are attending.
In his opening speech, Romanian President Ion Iliescu noted that 2004 is a particularly important year in terms of EU enlargement and consolidation of relations between Central and Eastern European countries within a broader regional context.
(Rompres, Nine O'Clock - 27/05/04)
